RX cards are known to have 1 or 2 memory states (3 if including 0 idle state). The highest state will be selected by default. In some rare cases, cards may fail to undervolt on the highest state thus requiring to select a lower one. For example, the highest is 2, thus if undervolting you would want to set state 1.
